                            <comment id="14728509" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 05:07:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user asfgit closed the pull request at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/169&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14728661" author="ijuma" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 08:12:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m a bit unclear about this. Normally, trace is the noisiest of all log levels, but in this case debug is more detailed than trace? Can you please share the reasoning?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729534" author="singhashish" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 18:33:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ijuma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ijuma&quot;&gt;ijuma&lt;/a&gt; Oops, I got it reversed. That&apos;s my bad. However, I feel that info actually fits at debug level as well. What do you think? Would you suggest I fix it as part of a separate JIRA or same JIRA. Thanks for pointing it out.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729540" author="gwenshap" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 18:37:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TRIVIAL pull request that doesn&apos;t require a JIRA makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729555" author="singhashish" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 18:45:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should I keep the detailed info in debug level as well? I am kind of in favor of that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729576" author="gwenshap" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 18:55:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, the reason we have two different log statements (one for trace and one for debug) is that the partition information can be HUGE on large clusters, and not always needed when diagnosing performance issues (the main use of this log). So we need one level with details (TRACE) and one level without (DEBUG).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729580" author="ijuma" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 18:57:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=singhashish&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;singhashish&quot;&gt;singhashish&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;ll let &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gwenshap&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gwenshap&quot;&gt;gwenshap&lt;/a&gt; comment on whether it should be available on both debug and trace or just trace. I don&apos;t have a strong opinion either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14729711" author="singhashish" created="Thu, 3 Sep 2015 20:22:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gwenshap&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gwenshap&quot;&gt;gwenshap&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ijuma&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ijuma&quot;&gt;ijuma&lt;/a&gt;, created &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/192&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/192&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
